Ok, there are three issues that I am seeing ([demo](http://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/njt1nth5/2/)):

1. The widgets file was being loaded before tablesorter, so it was causing a javascript error.
2. Don't use "updateAll" unless the content of the `thead` is changing.
3. Since the scroller widget is in a modal window, it was setting the width of the table to zero. Add a window resize event to the update callback to trigger it to recalculate the table dimensions and it will work.

   ```js
    $('#tableso').trigger('update', [true, function(){
        $(window).resize();
    }]);
    ```

    It still doesn't look great because the cells aren't lining up perfectly and the header is not getting narrowed by the scroll bar width. I'll have to look at that issue when I have more time.

Hi @Jade124889!

It works for me. I created [this demo](http://jsfiddle.net/bbxxomhx/107/) to demonstrate the use of:

* [`filter-select`](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-filter.html#classes) class name to convert the filter into a select dropdown.
* [`filter-match`](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-filter.html#classes) class name to only match the results in the table. This defaults to an exact match otherwise.
* `data-value` which sets the initial query. The data-attribute can be changed by setting the [`filter_defaultAttrib` option](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#widget-filter-defaultattrib).
* [`filter_selectSource`](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#widget-filter-selectsource) mostly because I wanted to show more than one result.

```html
<th data-value="abc" class="filter-select filter-match">AlphaNumeric</th>
```

```js
$(function() {
  $('table').tablesorter({
    theme: 'blue',
    widgets: ['zebra', 'filter'],
    widgetOptions: {
      filter_selectSource: {
        0: ['abc', 'zyx']
      }
    }
  });
});
```

