```
@given(integers())
@with_settings(Settings, Random)
def test_foo_bar(x):
    ...
```

And this actually helps to keep keyword arguments with no conflicts:
```
@given(x=integers())
@with_settings(Settings, Random)
def test_foo_bar(x):
    ...
```

Why not `with Settings():` ? Because if one day I decide to remove it, I have to reindent the whole block which will not make changes history clearer.

