Actually, reopening since this might not make it into the first iteration of the GA library.

I think the most appropriate place for this while preserving existing behavior will be to add an argument to the `.begin()` method of the various job classes. Example:

```
query_job = client.query(query_string)
query_job.begin(config_overrides={
        'destinationTable': {
            'projectId': 'some-project',
            'datasetId': 'some-dataset',
            'tableId': 'some-table'
        }
})
```

Any properties that appear in the `config_overrides` dictionary will be merged into the API resource representation before calling the jobs insert HTTP method.

