@gcongedo Rather than fiddling with the `$HOME` environment variable, I think it would be better to simply tell Ganga to store its information in a different location. You can either edit the `gangadir` variable in the `.gangarc` file (remember to take away the `#` at the beginning of the line), or you can simply start Ganga with a command line like

```
ganga -o'[Configuration]gangadir=/scratch/gcongedo/gangadir'
```

